<p>The <code>html</code> function escapes HTML special characters for safe display.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $htmlText | html{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{echo $htmlText | html}</b></p>

<h2>Escape Tags</h2>
<pre>{open}echo '<script>alert("XSS")</script>' | html{close}</pre>
<p>Safe: <b>{echo '<script>alert("XSS")</script>' | html}</b></p>

<h2>Escape Quotes</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'He said "hello"' | html{close}</pre>
<p>Escaped: <b>{echo 'He said "hello"' | html}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $htmlText | html | replace('&amp;', '+'){close}</pre>
<p>Modified: <b>{echo $htmlText | html | replace('&amp;', '+')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo '<b>Bold</b>' | html | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Escaped and upper: <b>{echo '<b>Bold</b>' | html | upper}</b></p>

<h2>Characters Escaped</h2>
<ul>
<li><code>&lt;</code> becomes <code>&amp;lt;</code></li>
<li><code>&gt;</code> becomes <code>&amp;gt;</code></li>
<li><code>&amp;</code> becomes <code>&amp;amp;</code></li>
<li><code>"</code> becomes <code>&amp;quot;</code></li>
</ul>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Always escape user input before displaying in HTML to prevent XSS attacks.</p>
